" {\n    \"title\": \"Reversed Words Checker (Hard)\",\n    \"description\": \"Write a function `is_reversed_words` that checks if the words in a given sentence are reversed when read backwards. The sentence can contain multiple words, spaces, punctuation, and numbers.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef is_reversed_words(s: str) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string that contains a sentence with multiple words, spaces, punctuation, and numbers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if the words in the input sentence are reversed when read backwards, `False` otherwise.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"import re\\ndef is_reversed_words(s: str) -> bool:\\n    # Split the string into words by space or punctuation\\n    words = re.findall(\\\"w+\\\", s)\\n    # Reverse the order of the list of words\\n    reversed_words = words[-1::-1]\\n    # Check if each word in the original list is the reverse of a corresponding word in the reversed list\\n    for i, word in enumerate(reversed_words):\\n        if word != s.rsplit(\\\" \\\", 1)[i][0][::-1] or len(word) != len(s.rsplit(\\\" \\\", 1)[i][0]):\\n            return False\\n    return True\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        'assert is_reversed_words(\"Hello, World!\") == False',\n        'assert is_reversed_words(\"olleH ,dlroW\") == True',\n        'assert is_reversed_words(\"I am a Palindrome tester.\") == False',\n        'assert is_reversed_words(\"tester.Palindrome ama I\") == True'\n    ]\n   }"